title.narrative: By 2020, HIV positive pregnant and lactating women and children better adhere to HIV treatment and related services

description.narrative: Access to quality services for women living with HIV and their HIV-exposed infants is a priority, and in 2021, UNICEF focused on strengthening and expanding innovative;interventions to identify, treat, and monitor the viral load of HIV-positive adults and adolescent mothers to reduce mother-to-child transmission along the full maternal-child health and prevention of mother to child transmission (PMTCT) spectrum. UNICEF also supported the implementation of re-testing (a recently approved national protocol) to timely identify HIV-infected mothers during the breastfeeding period, reaching over 8,900 women. | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:07/01/2022
